<h2 id="discussion-questions">Discussion Questions</h2>
<p class="lead">Start talking. Find a conversation starter for your group.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Do you know a selective listener? Are you one? Did you even hear this question?</li>
  <li>Do you have $5 obedience or $100 obedience? Share a story.</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start thinking. Ask questions to get your group thinking.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Three weeks into this series, what are some themes you notice playing out in your life?</li>
  <li>Read Haggai 2:12-14. What message is God sending through Haggai? How does it apply today?</li>
  <li>Think about verse 2:14 specifically. How much of what you do is defiled by sin? What does God want instead?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start sharing. Choose questions that create openness.</p>

<ul>
  <li>When you‚Äôre making the right choices, but life just doesn‚Äôt go your way, how do you respond?</li>
  <li>How current are you in your obedience to God? Is there anything on a waiting list?</li>
  <li>What is one thing you‚Äôre really struggling to trust God with? How could you give that part of your heart to Him?</li>
  <li>What hard things are happening to you that could be an opportunity to grow closer to God?</li>
</ul>

<p class="lead">Start praying. Be bold, and pray specifically.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Father, We want to learn to obey You out of our love for You. Holy Spirit, teach us to trust, show us how to believe, and strengthen us to obey. Jesus, You are the only one who makes dirty things clean. Do Your work in us. Amen.</li>
</ul>

